<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-15T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-15T03:35:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.01/93: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-15T12:00:00+03:25">December
                                    15, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1122. Prime Minister Soheily resigned yesterday. It is thought this is
                            merely a tactical move to enable him to eliminate certain members of
                            Cabinet and that Shah will request him to form a new government in next
                            few days. Soheily has been talking of a reorganization for months but
                            has apparently been unable persuade men concerned to resign.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>